messages.message: An accompanying docs update & release notes makes complete sense for this. Once we add a fixVersion to the Jira ticket (can we estimate 25.24 or 25.26?) this will be flagged for review by the docs team, and they'd make a corresponding docs ticket to action before this is released.
Should I do anything specific to mark it for the docs team review?
I think just the fixVersion will flag it for them
but we can always tag @Chris Cowell or @jean on the ticket to be sure

Cool, thanks!
(I just use my onboarding tickets to figure out all processes and how things are working there)
